news.title: Seizure notices sent to 3,000 property owners in Kolhapur
news.para: The KMC has decided to take stern steps in order to reach as close to the property tax collection target as possible as the financial year is about to end in less than a month.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP intensifies drive against illegal construction, three booked
news.para: Kavita Ambwani, Sunita Vardhan — both residents of Delhi — and Prateek Khandelwal have been booked under Section 10 of Haryana Development and Regulation of Urban Areas Act, 1975.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Builder, family members arrested for duping buyers of over Rs 100 crore
news.para: ​The builder, Raj Kumar Jain, was running two companies named Red Apple and Idea builders. He is accused of borrowing money from people, enticing them by promising to pay a high rate of interest of them, City Superintendent of Police (1st) Nipun Agarwal said.

news.title: Companies trying hard to make office premises Covid-safe
news.para: Developers, facility management firms devise and implement plans to meet Covid protocols and minimise the chances of virus spread.

news.title: NCLT allows withdrawal of insolvency proceedings against Nirmal Lifestyle
news.para: NCLT had admitted the company under the Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process (CIRP) last year based on a petition filed by IDBI Trusteeship Services, on behalf of Altico Capital, after the company defaulted on its dues worth Rs 286 crore.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh hopes to speed up realisation of RCs issued by RERA in next fiscal year
news.para: Data up to January 2021 shows that in Uttar Pradesh, out of a total 2,177 RCs that were issued since the inception of Rera in 2018, only 353 were realised by district administrations.

news.title: HC allows ED to contact US in money laundering probe against DHFL promoters
news.para: ​​The brothers own an apartment in New York, which the ED submitted represents proceeds of crime and was attached by it.

news.title: Indian ultra HNIs allocate 29% of wealth to buy primary, second homes in 2021
news.para: ​In its attitude survey, part of the Wealth Report 2022, property consultant Knight Frank India said that 29 per cent wealth of Indian UHNWIs, those having a net worth of USD 30 million and above), is allocated towards purchase of principal and second homes.

news.title: North Delhi civic body extends last date for payment of property tax with amnesty scheme
news.para: Chairman of Standing Committee of the North Delhi Municipal Corporation (NDMC) Jogi Ram Jain said the civic body has extended the last date for availing its amnesty scheme from February 28 to March 31.

news.title: Revised building bylaws in Secunderabad cantonment board areas in three months
news.para: The Ministry of Defence (MoD) has finalised the revised building bylaws sent by the officials of the Secunderabad Cantonment Board (SCB).

news.title: CPPIB to invest Rs 2,650 crore in JV with RMZ Corp to develop commercial assets
news.para: The joint venture will be seeded with StarTech – a 1.37 million-sq-ft Grade A office building located in Koramangala, Bengaluru, which is currently co-owned by RMZ and Prestige Estates. CPPIB will acquire Prestige’s entire stake in StarTech.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM opens loan drive for OTS beneficiaries
news.para: The chief minister stated that providing loans would benefit the OTS beneficiaries to a greater extent and handed over the cheques to the beneficiaries of Guntur municipal corporation.

news.title: Chandigarh: Citco to rent out 48 transit flats in Hotel Parkview
news.para: Earlier, Citco was planning to construct the city’s biggest convention centre at the hotel, using the space of the flats and readying a blueprint.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Discom offers EMI scheme for dual meters in highrises
news.para: With few takers for the scheme in Ghaziabad four years on, the power department — Paschimanchal Vidyut Vitran Nigam Ltd (PVVNL) — is offering a sort of concession by allowing people to pay the compulsory one-time deposit of Rs 20,000 in 12 EMIs.

news.title: Dalmia Cements' MD fears ED may use his own statement against him
news.para: Puneet is one of the accused in the CBI’s Dalmia Cements chargesheet filed in the quid pro quo case. When the ED began its probe into the same episode and summoned him under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act, he approached the high court challenging it.
